title: Pip dependency resolver for colab
body:
### Is there an existing issue for this?

- [X] I have searched the existing issues

### Bug description

At the 'pip install' step of colab, I am getting this message for several download steps: "INFO: pip is looking at multiple versions of tqdm to determine which version is compatible with other requirements. This could take a while." In this case, it's referring to tqdm, but this is happening for several programs (opencv_python_headless, imageio, decorator, imageio_ffmpeg, moviepy, kiwisolver). The script then downloads several versions of the program, then generates this message: "INFO: This is taking longer than usual. You might need to provide the dependency resolver with stricter constraints to reduce runtime. If you want to abort this run, you can press Ctrl + C to do so. To improve how pip performs, tell us what happened here: https://pip.pypa.io/surveys/backtracking". I've allowed this procedure to run for several hours, but it never completes this initial step. I have successfully run colab on this machine within the past two months. I have recently redownloaded conda and python on this machine to resolve some other issues. I don't know why that would affect the program in colab, but mentioning in case it's not just a coincidence. I'm having the same issue on other machines.  
    


### Operating System

Windows 10 Pro

### DeepLabCut version

colab

### DeepLabCut mode

single animal

### Device type

gpu

### Steps To Reproduce

1. Run the first cell in colab:
!pip install git+https://github.com/DeepLabCut/DeepLabCut-core.git@tf2.2alpha
!pip install tf_slim

### Relevant log output
